<TITLE> 'Thief' dies from mob beating in Barisal </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Barisal, June 3 (bdnews24.com)Villagers of Chhoto Dumuria in Agailjharha upazila, Barisal, beat a suspected burglar to death and critically injured another early on Wednesday, police said. The dead man was identified as Kamrul Islam Mridha, 28, originally from Kalkini in Madaripur. Kamrul's cousin Abul Bashar, 25, seriously injured in the beating, has been admitted to Agailjharha Thana Health Complex. Agailjharha police chief Ashok Kumar Nandi told bdnews24.com that a gang of suspected burglars broke into a house at 2:30am. The house-owner's son Helal Byapari caught Kamrul Islam, a member of the dacoit band, and started yelling. "As the villagers caught up with Abul Bashar, another member of the fleeing gang, they beat them both mercilessly," said the police chief. Kamrul succumbed to his injuries at the scene, he said. The body has been sent to Sher-e-Bangla Medical College for autopsy, he added. bdn
